sentences: Róża Etkin (1908 in Warsaw – 16 January 1945 in Warsaw), known after marriage as Róża Etkin-Moszkowska, was a Polish pianist.
She was a pupil of Aleksander Michałowski and Zbigniew Drzewiecki in Warsaw.
During the early 1930s she settled in Berlin to study with Professor Moritz Mayer-Mahr.
